1
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:05,650
"Entry Gate"

2
00:00:05,700 --> 00:00:07,220
They're off all at once!

3
00:00:07,550 --> 00:00:10,810
The current order is
Blue, Yellow, Red, and White.

4
00:00:10,870 --> 00:00:15,840
Go, Niko! Nice!

5
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:19,070
No change as the baton goes
to the second runner.

6
00:00:19,340 --> 00:00:22,000
It's our last sports day,
so we absolutely can't lose.

7
00:00:22,050 --> 00:00:25,500
- Go!
- Toyo!

8
00:00:25,660 --> 00:00:28,100
Blue, Yellow, and Red
are in a close race!

9
00:00:28,220 --> 00:00:31,620
- Go!
- Let's go!

10
00:00:35,910 --> 00:00:38,130
I hope the baton pass goes well...

11
00:00:38,760 --> 00:00:42,170
- No change as the baton goes to the third runner.
- Yukki! Here you go!

12
00:00:50,450 --> 00:00:52,640
Red passed Yellow
and moves into second place!

13
00:00:52,700 --> 00:00:54,840
Yukki, good job!
Keep it up!

14
00:00:55,380 --> 00:00:56,330
Tabo!

15
00:00:57,690 --> 00:00:58,970
Full throttle!

16
00:00:59,660 --> 00:01:01,536
- Go, Tabo!
- Go, go!

17
00:01:02,200 --> 00:01:04,720
Oh man...
I ate too much lunch.

18
00:01:05,530 --> 00:01:08,010
- Hang in there!!
- Oh no, we got passed!

19
00:01:12,220 --> 00:01:13,240
It's okay.

20
00:01:13,750 --> 00:01:16,660
We've practiced so much.
We're definitely not going to lose!

21
00:01:16,720 --> 00:01:17,780
King!

22
00:01:17,910 --> 00:01:19,040
Go!

23
00:01:20,910 --> 00:01:22,220
The rest is up to you, King!

24
00:01:25,320 --> 00:01:26,720
Leave the final leg to me!

25
00:02:08,230 --> 00:02:09,100
Yukki.

26
00:02:10,620 --> 00:02:11,460
Thank you.

27
00:02:16,490 --> 00:02:18,290
Ah, that's Saruhashi, right?

28
00:02:18,930 --> 00:02:21,920
- Ah, that's Saruhashi.
- Be quiet.

29
00:02:38,250 --> 00:02:39,810
Mom...!

30
00:03:03,340 --> 00:03:10,250
THE RIGHT TO JUDGE

31
00:04:26,650 --> 00:04:29,760
I never thought
we'd meet again like this.

32
00:04:30,850 --> 00:04:31,870
Yeah, right.

33
00:04:32,530 --> 00:04:34,450
But are you okay?

34
00:04:35,330 --> 00:04:38,030
- Huh?
- That article.

35
00:04:39,310 --> 00:04:42,620
Of course,
I don't think Saruhashi did it.

36
00:04:43,460 --> 00:04:48,990
But it's true that everyone who was blacked out
in the yearbook has died.

37
00:04:50,040 --> 00:04:52,470
Aren't Tabo and King in danger too?

38
00:04:55,760 --> 00:04:58,110
Isn't there anything we can do?

39
00:04:58,590 --> 00:05:00,000
Even something small. Anything.

40
00:05:00,160 --> 00:05:02,650
Yeah. Let's reach out to
everyone in the class...

41
00:05:02,830 --> 00:05:03,870
Cut it out.

42
00:05:06,720 --> 00:05:08,400
I don't even want to say this,

43
00:05:09,340 --> 00:05:10,490
but because of you guys,

44
00:05:10,610 --> 00:05:12,250
the police questioned me,

45
00:05:12,660 --> 00:05:14,470
and people at work have been talking.

46
00:05:15,450 --> 00:05:16,970
Honestly, it's a pain.

47
00:05:17,530 --> 00:05:19,000
That’s an awful thing to say...

48
00:05:19,300 --> 00:05:20,930
This is a class issue, isn’t it?

49
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:22,220
No, it’s not.

50
00:05:23,480 --> 00:05:27,710
This is the problem of the ones
who were doing the bullying.

51
00:05:28,360 --> 00:05:31,000
It has nothing to do with us. Right?

52
00:05:32,400 --> 00:05:35,220
- You can't just say it has nothing to do with us.
- I'm scared.

53
00:05:36,500 --> 00:05:41,340
That yearbook came up at the reunion,
and then the incidents started happening.

54
00:05:43,700 --> 00:05:45,900
I kept telling myself
I had nothing to do with it.

55
00:05:46,650 --> 00:05:48,620
So maybe I can't just say
I'm not involved.

56
00:05:50,570 --> 00:05:52,840
So maybe I can't just say
I'm not involved.

57
00:05:55,590 --> 00:05:58,000
I might be killed too.

58
00:06:00,240 --> 00:06:04,720
And what if something
happens to my family?

59
00:06:16,130 --> 00:06:16,950
King.

60
00:06:19,860 --> 00:06:21,990
About earlier, I'm sorry.

61
00:06:22,890 --> 00:06:25,280
No, Yukki, you don't
need to apologize.

62
00:06:25,500 --> 00:06:27,060
But still...

63
00:06:28,930 --> 00:06:31,610
is there anything we can do?

64
00:06:32,180 --> 00:06:37,040
Even if everyone else can’t,
at least we want to help.

65
00:06:42,290 --> 00:06:44,380
Don't count me out
because I'm a housewife.

66
00:06:44,650 --> 00:06:46,960
I can step up
when it counts. Right?

67
00:06:47,260 --> 00:06:49,720
Yeah. And I've got that too...

68
00:06:50,910 --> 00:06:52,100
I'm a top hairstylist.

69
00:06:52,500 --> 00:06:54,140
- Isn’t that kind of old-school?
- Really?

70
00:06:54,190 --> 00:06:55,570
Yeah, see?

71
00:06:57,310 --> 00:07:02,340
Wait... weren’t we
the relay team back then?

72
00:07:02,570 --> 00:07:05,180
- Oh! That's right!
- See!

73
00:07:05,720 --> 00:07:09,630
Well, we’ve aged,
but I think we can still be helpful.

74
00:07:09,870 --> 00:07:10,830
Enough.

75
00:07:15,090 --> 00:07:17,520
Like they said,
it’s our fault.

76
00:07:18,880 --> 00:07:20,420
So let it go.

77
00:07:21,690 --> 00:07:22,700
No, it’s not enough.

78
00:07:23,580 --> 00:07:24,930
Not at all.

79
00:07:25,940 --> 00:07:27,600
You said it yourself back then,

80
00:07:27,720 --> 00:07:29,590
you weren't going to give up.

81
00:07:29,660 --> 00:07:31,490
When are you even talking about?

82
00:07:32,780 --> 00:07:33,940
This isn’t a game.

83
00:07:35,330 --> 00:07:37,770
I didn’t mean it like that...

84
00:07:40,320 --> 00:07:43,950
Anyway, this has
nothing to do with you.

85
00:07:44,620 --> 00:07:45,990
So don’t get involved anymore.

86
00:08:04,970 --> 00:08:07,350
No word from Chonmage.

87
00:08:08,570 --> 00:08:10,470
Damn it...

88
00:08:10,700 --> 00:08:12,570
At least give us a sign.

89
00:08:20,130 --> 00:08:24,200
There’s a way to treat someone
who’s reaching out to help.

90
00:08:26,100 --> 00:08:27,900
They've got to be scared too.

91
00:08:28,640 --> 00:08:30,530
But still, they're thinking about us.

92
00:08:30,650 --> 00:08:31,740
Exactly...

93
00:08:35,690 --> 00:08:37,820
They don’t have to worry about us.

94
00:08:38,790 --> 00:08:39,710
Right?

95
00:08:41,130 --> 00:08:43,280
Toyo and Yukki have their own lives.

96
00:08:44,780 --> 00:08:46,580
If we drag them in,
they could get killed.

97
00:08:47,800 --> 00:08:49,750
We don’t even know
what Chonmage is doing.

98
00:08:52,590 --> 00:08:54,730
If it means dragging
anyone else into this...

99
00:08:57,570 --> 00:09:00,400
What the hell...
What does that mean?

100
00:09:01,700 --> 00:09:03,020
Are we just going to give up?

101
00:09:08,300 --> 00:09:10,220
We'll find Chonmage, and

102
00:09:10,960 --> 00:09:12,470
we'll end this incident.

103
00:09:14,060 --> 00:09:15,050
Right?

104
00:09:18,280 --> 00:09:20,060
Shut up.
Just leave me alone.

105
00:09:30,970 --> 00:09:33,220
What can one person
even do on their own?

106
00:09:45,890 --> 00:09:47,570
- By the way...
- Yes?

107
00:09:47,810 --> 00:09:51,790
Has anything been up with Mr. Haryu
on the first floor lately?

108
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:53,540
Yes.

109
00:09:56,570 --> 00:09:57,090
Yes.

110
00:09:59,070 --> 00:10:01,100
- Excuse us for a moment.
- Hey... What do you want?

111
00:10:01,300 --> 00:10:04,190
Please stop.
I haven’t done anything...

112
00:10:06,450 --> 00:10:07,130
Oh...!

113
00:10:22,950 --> 00:10:25,290
Alright... Well then.

114
00:10:32,920 --> 00:10:35,540
I'll let you know as soon as
I find out anything Mr. Haryu.

115
00:10:36,480 --> 00:10:39,780
But honestly, his phone is off,
and it's looking more and more like

116
00:10:40,140 --> 00:10:42,260
he disappeared on his own.

117
00:10:43,460 --> 00:10:44,720
Give me a bit more time.

118
00:10:45,470 --> 00:10:46,150
Got it.

119
00:10:52,430 --> 00:10:56,450
I know I keep my job
under wraps, but maybe

120
00:10:57,880 --> 00:10:59,950
I should've told you
I was a detective sooner.

121
00:11:00,640 --> 00:11:02,800
Don't worry about it.
You had no choice.

122
00:11:03,430 --> 00:11:04,930
Having you here is a big relief.

123
00:11:11,290 --> 00:11:12,220
Thanks.

124
00:11:19,500 --> 00:11:20,190
Look,

125
00:11:22,940 --> 00:11:24,600
I’m telling you this not as a detective,

126
00:11:25,330 --> 00:11:26,890
but as a friend.

127
00:11:29,290 --> 00:11:32,570
There’s a possibility people around you
might get dragged into this.

128
00:11:33,820 --> 00:11:35,510
Of course, we’re doing

129
00:11:35,670 --> 00:11:38,620
everything we can to close this case
as fast as possible.

130
00:11:40,180 --> 00:11:41,090
But please,

131
00:11:44,050 --> 00:11:45,440
just be careful.

132
00:11:53,390 --> 00:11:54,220
Promise me.

133
00:11:56,700 --> 00:11:57,560
Thank you. I will.

134
00:12:09,880 --> 00:12:10,720
Hey.

135
00:12:13,380 --> 00:12:15,710
Dad, you're late. Finally.

136
00:12:17,230 --> 00:12:19,460
So, I'm trying to decide between

137
00:12:19,500 --> 00:12:21,340
the zoo and the amusement park.

138
00:12:22,930 --> 00:12:24,520
Yeah, shopping sounds good too.

139
00:12:24,670 --> 00:12:27,170
What if something
happens to my family?

140
00:12:27,880 --> 00:12:31,120
There’s a possibility people around you
might get dragged into this.

141
00:12:33,770 --> 00:12:34,530
Dad?

142
00:12:36,070 --> 00:12:37,050
Dad.

143
00:12:38,730 --> 00:12:39,900
Let’s go!

144
00:12:40,030 --> 00:12:42,100
Kanon, leave that toy piano here.

145
00:12:42,400 --> 00:12:44,980
- Okay.
- Why do you even want to bring that?

146
00:12:45,810 --> 00:12:47,100
- Let's go.
- Yeah.

147
00:12:47,160 --> 00:12:48,740
Be careful, okay? Have fun.

148
00:12:48,920 --> 00:12:50,480
- We will!
- I'll go change. Sorry.

149
00:12:54,790 --> 00:12:57,090
Huh? Are you working today?

150
00:12:58,210 --> 00:13:00,060
Yeah. Didn’t I tell you?

151
00:13:02,410 --> 00:13:04,610
I can't find my yellow Ferris wheel tie.

152
00:13:11,690 --> 00:13:15,470
Huh? Yamato?
Hey, where are you going?

153
00:13:15,740 --> 00:13:16,600
Out.

154
00:13:16,990 --> 00:13:19,720
Hey, let me know when you know
what time you're coming home.

155
00:13:20,740 --> 00:13:22,860
Oh, wait. Here.

156
00:13:22,920 --> 00:13:24,540
- Look for the tie, okay?
- Here.

157
00:14:03,640 --> 00:14:07,260
I'm telling you,
your client turnover is too slow.

158
00:14:08,370 --> 00:14:10,730
You need to think more
from a business standpoint.

159
00:14:13,260 --> 00:14:14,320
I'm sorry...

160
00:14:15,950 --> 00:14:17,370
If you're not making enough,

161
00:14:17,640 --> 00:14:20,100
I can close
this salon anytime. Got it?

162
00:14:24,970 --> 00:14:26,900
You don’t really get it.

163
00:14:29,300 --> 00:14:31,600
Anyway, I'm parking illegally,
so I've gotta run.

164
00:15:03,440 --> 00:15:04,270
Wow!

165
00:15:04,420 --> 00:15:06,270
No one’s here. It's all ours!

166
00:15:06,350 --> 00:15:07,200
Awesome!

167
00:15:08,600 --> 00:15:09,850
Kanon, I'm sorry.

168
00:15:11,290 --> 00:15:13,890
Oh! I’m gonna practice
my back hip circle.

169
00:15:14,070 --> 00:15:16,890
I’m always too embarrassed to try it
when everyone’s watching.

170
00:15:17,460 --> 00:15:19,480
Dad, watch me, okay?

171
00:15:20,320 --> 00:15:20,970
Yeah.

172
00:15:25,870 --> 00:15:29,470
Damn...
where the hell is he?

173
00:15:34,300 --> 00:15:34,910
Hm?

174
00:15:39,410 --> 00:15:41,710
Is this...?

175
00:15:43,250 --> 00:15:44,580
Yes! Got it!

176
00:15:44,640 --> 00:15:46,480
Nooo, I lost!

177
00:15:47,760 --> 00:15:49,960
-Again.
- Let’s play again!

178
00:15:50,560 --> 00:15:53,050
Stop filming and
hurry up, Chonmage!

179
00:15:53,380 --> 00:15:54,930
Alright, let’s do this!
Here we go!

180
00:15:57,920 --> 00:16:00,640
Tat tat tat tat...

181
00:16:01,170 --> 00:16:04,340
Why? Why?

182
00:16:04,560 --> 00:16:07,620
Why are we in the river?

183
00:16:08,320 --> 00:16:10,470
Go over there quickly.

184
00:16:10,670 --> 00:16:12,990
Drive B! B B B!

185
00:16:16,160 --> 00:16:17,600
Stop it.

186
00:16:17,950 --> 00:16:20,140
- Whoa, whoa!
- Look!

187
00:16:20,770 --> 00:16:23,200
Like this...

188
00:16:23,440 --> 00:16:24,550
These guys...

189
00:16:29,130 --> 00:16:30,180
Ready...

190
00:16:30,310 --> 00:16:32,530
One day Hin

191
00:16:32,800 --> 00:16:35,030
In the forest Kantaro

192
00:16:35,140 --> 00:16:37,200
A bear and Niko

193
00:16:37,430 --> 00:16:39,490
Met Tabo

194
00:16:39,610 --> 00:16:43,990
A forest path in bloom with Chonmage

195
00:16:44,040 --> 00:16:48,590
A bear met Taka-King!

196
00:16:49,640 --> 00:16:50,300
Hm?

197
00:16:57,300 --> 00:16:58,430
Ready...

198
00:16:58,510 --> 00:17:00,810
One day Hin

199
00:17:01,010 --> 00:17:03,250
In the forest Kantaro

200
00:17:45,820 --> 00:17:48,230
- Oh, hey.
- Hi.

201
00:17:55,690 --> 00:17:57,880
Ms. Saruhashi, are you okay?

202
00:17:59,290 --> 00:18:00,030
Well...

203
00:18:02,900 --> 00:18:06,040
You've been through a lot.
You should take some time off.

204
00:18:06,600 --> 00:18:10,020
You want to keep working
because of everything that’s happened, right?

205
00:18:10,740 --> 00:18:11,410
Yeah.

206
00:18:12,500 --> 00:18:13,310
But this...

207
00:18:14,890 --> 00:18:16,310
Whoa...

208
00:18:16,470 --> 00:18:20,860
Vice Minister Sato, Minister Kato's
affair partner, is getting divorced.

209
00:18:21,010 --> 00:18:23,060
- Go get a direct comment from Sato.
- Yes.

210
00:18:23,470 --> 00:18:24,910
I’ll have them got right away.

211
00:18:25,060 --> 00:18:26,240
Sonoko, I'm sorry.

212
00:18:27,190 --> 00:18:28,460
Matsui, let’s go.

213
00:18:29,610 --> 00:18:30,380
Yes.

214
00:18:33,170 --> 00:18:36,380
"103 Haryu"

215
00:18:37,110 --> 00:18:40,110
Whoa, you really surprised me.

216
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:46,090
Tell me about it. Right?

217
00:18:46,340 --> 00:18:47,250
Yeah.

218
00:18:48,280 --> 00:18:49,780
I got so freaked out!

219
00:18:54,210 --> 00:18:58,290
I can't believe
Chonmage went missing...

220
00:19:01,730 --> 00:19:03,120
It’s my fault.

221
00:19:05,850 --> 00:19:07,860
- If I'd just been paying attention to him...
- Hey,

222
00:19:09,030 --> 00:19:11,090
can you stop saying that?

223
00:19:14,180 --> 00:19:17,560
You and King are carrying
too much on your own.

224
00:19:19,310 --> 00:19:22,310
- But...
- Are we really that unreliable?

225
00:19:22,550 --> 00:19:26,430
No, it’s not that.
It's not about being unreliable.

226
00:19:27,320 --> 00:19:29,500
King and I don’t want to
drag you guys into this.

227
00:19:30,190 --> 00:19:31,890
Seriously, people have died.

228
00:19:32,650 --> 00:19:34,040
It's dangerous.

229
00:19:35,690 --> 00:19:37,110
And me too...

230
00:19:39,150 --> 00:19:41,160
never mind.

231
00:19:43,160 --> 00:19:45,870
You two have your lives now,

232
00:19:46,660 --> 00:19:50,300
I don't want you to lose the dreams
you finally achieved because of us.

233
00:19:54,410 --> 00:19:57,030
It just wasn’t right, huh?

234
00:19:59,860 --> 00:20:02,810
Sure, I did became a wife.

235
00:20:03,410 --> 00:20:08,320
But something felt off.

236
00:20:09,010 --> 00:20:10,510
Maybe I was naive.

237
00:20:13,690 --> 00:20:18,110
I've lost count of how many times
I looked the other way when my husband cheated.

238
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:23,200
I kept telling myself,
"At least until my kid's grown."

239
00:20:25,370 --> 00:20:30,240
But by then, I'll probably
be cut off from the world.

240
00:20:31,080 --> 00:20:35,510
No job. No friends to hang out with.

241
00:20:36,470 --> 00:20:40,230
And I don't even have the strength
to divorce him and start over on my own.

242
00:20:42,570 --> 00:20:44,380
It wasn't what
I thought it'd be at all.

243
00:20:47,770 --> 00:20:49,240
Me neither.

244
00:20:51,650 --> 00:20:54,440
I can't exactly call myself
some "star hairstylist."

245
00:20:55,930 --> 00:21:00,090
I'm just a hired manager,
getting lectured about sales

246
00:21:00,170 --> 00:21:03,920
by an owner younger than me,
bowing my head every day.

247
00:21:06,870 --> 00:21:08,540
The stress is gonna
make me go bald.

248
00:21:09,750 --> 00:21:11,610
I see...

249
00:21:11,780 --> 00:21:14,390
- Don’t "I see" me.
- My bad.

250
00:21:15,890 --> 00:21:18,110
I guess everyone's dealing
with their own stuff.

251
00:21:18,570 --> 00:21:19,920
But still...

252
00:21:20,110 --> 00:21:21,630
We decided
we're not giving up.

253
00:21:24,450 --> 00:21:25,330
Right?

254
00:21:26,440 --> 00:21:29,310
Yeah. I just remembered something.

255
00:21:36,470 --> 00:21:38,270
Don’t cry, Yukki.

256
00:21:39,390 --> 00:21:40,400
I know...

257
00:21:41,280 --> 00:21:45,710
But we lost,
and it was our last one...

258
00:21:56,650 --> 00:21:58,300
Next time, we’ll definitely not lose.

259
00:21:59,470 --> 00:22:01,300
Huh? Next time?

260
00:22:02,040 --> 00:22:04,310
Next time? It was our...

261
00:22:06,870 --> 00:22:08,660
Next time, we’ll definitely win!

262
00:22:10,220 --> 00:22:12,030
Even though it was our last sports day,

263
00:22:12,270 --> 00:22:13,740
King said, "Next time we’ll win."

264
00:22:13,810 --> 00:22:15,850
He wasn't giving up at all.

265
00:22:16,060 --> 00:22:17,170
Yeah, exactly.

266
00:22:17,790 --> 00:22:21,110
That's why it didn't
even feel like we lost.

267
00:22:25,650 --> 00:22:28,140
I think... somewhere along the way,
I'd already given up.

268
00:22:31,190 --> 00:22:34,830
Like, "Maybe this is all
my life's ever gonna be."

269
00:22:40,550 --> 00:22:41,390
But...

270
00:22:44,720 --> 00:22:47,320
we're done giving up.

271
00:22:48,610 --> 00:22:49,610
Right?

272
00:22:50,200 --> 00:22:51,190
Yeah.

273
00:22:52,670 --> 00:22:57,480
That’s why the two of us have been
reaching out to our old classmates.

274
00:22:58,360 --> 00:23:00,060
Reaching out...

275
00:23:00,930 --> 00:23:02,570
Are you guys serious?

276
00:23:03,570 --> 00:23:06,410
Well, looks like you guys
were already doing that,

277
00:23:06,620 --> 00:23:08,360
so we didn't get much out of it.

278
00:23:09,440 --> 00:23:13,450
But if they see that we're still
fighting and not giving up,

279
00:23:13,970 --> 00:23:16,870
maybe they'll decide to help.

280
00:23:18,710 --> 00:23:19,730
More than anything,

281
00:23:20,620 --> 00:23:27,490
I don’t want you, King, or
Saruhashi to disappear.

282
00:23:40,520 --> 00:23:41,770
I can’t do this anymore.

283
00:23:43,390 --> 00:23:45,710
One more time. Alright...

284
00:23:46,240 --> 00:23:48,380
Ready... go!

285
00:24:02,100 --> 00:24:03,170
Sorry.

286
00:24:05,270 --> 00:24:08,120
No, that’s not it.

287
00:24:10,820 --> 00:24:12,090
Thank you.

288
00:24:17,520 --> 00:24:19,810
This isn't over yet, right?

289
00:24:20,400 --> 00:24:22,940
Yeah. We're almost there.

290
00:24:23,510 --> 00:24:25,890
Alright. Let’s go.

291
00:24:27,000 --> 00:24:29,170
I picked up a lead too.

292
00:24:30,160 --> 00:24:33,960
So let’s give it one more push.

293
00:24:34,620 --> 00:24:35,610
All of us.

294
00:24:37,390 --> 00:24:38,200
Yeah.

295
00:24:42,890 --> 00:24:44,360
- Can you?
- Sure.

296
00:25:04,724 --> 00:25:07,540
- Give us a proper comment!
- Don’t run away!

297
00:25:07,860 --> 00:25:10,020
Did you take revenge on the bullies?

298
00:25:11,970 --> 00:25:13,380
Aren’t you getting in?

299
00:25:14,780 --> 00:25:16,360
Sorry, please go ahead.

300
00:25:24,430 --> 00:25:26,200
Thanks for waiting.

301
00:25:28,410 --> 00:25:30,290
Wait... what is it?

302
00:25:30,460 --> 00:25:31,930
Hello! Yojiro.

303
00:25:34,380 --> 00:25:36,770
I need to ask you something.
Come over here!

304
00:25:37,830 --> 00:25:38,470
Ah, no...

305
00:25:38,690 --> 00:25:40,510
Don't "no" me!
I know you were waiting for us!

306
00:25:45,410 --> 00:25:48,520
- Sorry it took so long to find it.
- I'm sorry, too.

307
00:25:48,750 --> 00:25:51,210
- Thank you so much.
- Thank you.

308
00:25:52,270 --> 00:25:53,110
Anyway, I'm busy, so...

309
00:25:53,540 --> 00:25:55,160
- Thank you so much.
- Thank you.

310
00:25:58,640 --> 00:25:59,960
Here, Kanon.
Have some water.

311
00:26:01,800 --> 00:26:03,430
Ready to go?

312
00:26:03,980 --> 00:26:05,060
One more time.

313
00:26:07,290 --> 00:26:08,550
Let me see...

314
00:26:09,320 --> 00:26:10,700
Oh, you’ve got a blister.

315
00:26:10,970 --> 00:26:12,740
I'm okay. It doesn’t hurt.

316
00:26:18,160 --> 00:26:20,510
- Oh!
- I did it!

317
00:26:20,910 --> 00:26:21,760
I did it!

318
00:26:21,870 --> 00:26:24,320
- You did it! Yay! Kanon!
- I did it! Yay! Ouch.

319
00:26:24,440 --> 00:26:26,620
Ah, sorry...
That was amazing.

320
00:26:26,770 --> 00:26:29,630
- Yeah. One more time.
- Yeah, while it's fresh!

321
00:26:32,030 --> 00:26:33,880
- Whoa-hoo!
- I did it!

322
00:26:33,910 --> 00:26:35,380
You’ve really gotten it now.

323
00:26:35,460 --> 00:26:36,800
- One more time?
- Perfect!

324
00:26:37,000 --> 00:26:39,250
Perfect. You've mastered
the back hip circle.

325
00:26:39,340 --> 00:26:40,250
- I did it!
- Yeah.

326
00:26:40,420 --> 00:26:41,510
I'm gonna tell my mom.

327
00:26:41,580 --> 00:26:44,250
Let’s buy something tasty
on the way home.

328
00:26:44,400 --> 00:26:45,450
Sounds good!

329
00:26:45,500 --> 00:26:47,500
"Imakuni"

330
00:26:48,690 --> 00:26:51,720
- Here.
- Oh, so this is the place?

331
00:26:51,840 --> 00:26:53,670
- Ah, welcome!
- Thank you for having us!

332
00:26:53,770 --> 00:26:55,410
Oh, welcome.

333
00:26:56,880 --> 00:26:57,800
What?

334
00:26:58,820 --> 00:27:01,010
Saruhashi?

335
00:27:01,480 --> 00:27:02,550
Why are you here?

336
00:27:04,500 --> 00:27:07,970
She'd been spending her nights alone
and couldn't take it anymore.

337
00:27:09,090 --> 00:27:10,910
So she ended up coming here.

338
00:27:11,100 --> 00:27:12,280
Yes. That’s right.

339
00:27:12,730 --> 00:27:14,640
Saruhashi, you're the best.

340
00:27:14,780 --> 00:27:16,930
Could you give us a hand?

341
00:27:17,160 --> 00:27:18,630
- Well then, I’ll give you this.
- Huh?

342
00:27:18,810 --> 00:27:20,330
I'll give you the whole thing.

343
00:27:22,160 --> 00:27:26,034
I found the SNS accounts
for the last few,

344
00:27:26,414 --> 00:27:29,019
but they live out of town.
So meeting them might be tough.

345
00:27:30,470 --> 00:27:33,430
Nope. I can’t get through
on the phone either.

346
00:27:33,600 --> 00:27:36,280
Well, a lot of them
probably don’t have landlines.

347
00:27:36,470 --> 00:27:38,600
Hey, can I borrow this for a sec?

348
00:27:39,030 --> 00:27:41,640
Their favorite TV shows
and songs are nostalgic,

349
00:27:41,840 --> 00:27:44,530
but not really helpful.

350
00:27:45,420 --> 00:27:47,060
What's this
"Which team are you?" thing?!

351
00:27:47,360 --> 00:27:49,650
Well, I’m a cat person. Meow.

352
00:27:49,830 --> 00:27:52,310
- Woof woof!
- You're a dog person.

353
00:27:53,000 --> 00:27:54,620
Wow, this is so nostalgic!

354
00:27:54,910 --> 00:27:56,740
Girl’s must-have item!

355
00:27:57,280 --> 00:27:59,130
What is this? A notebook?

356
00:27:59,800 --> 00:28:01,290
- A profile book.
- Huh?

357
00:28:01,450 --> 00:28:03,460
It was popular when we were kids.

358
00:28:03,690 --> 00:28:05,680
You’d write each other’s profiles.

359
00:28:05,900 --> 00:28:08,290
They even included
phone numbers and addresses.

360
00:28:08,580 --> 00:28:10,390
That’s kind of
personal info overload.

361
00:28:10,640 --> 00:28:11,780
That's how it was.

362
00:28:11,900 --> 00:28:15,260
You’d even write down
the initials of your crush.

363
00:28:15,460 --> 00:28:17,690
- Ah!
- Um...

364
00:28:18,780 --> 00:28:21,200
- Are there any initial?
- Not exactly initials.

365
00:28:21,280 --> 00:28:21,870
Huh?

366
00:28:23,120 --> 00:28:24,060
Is this...?

367
00:28:27,680 --> 00:28:28,980
Chonmage...

368
00:28:32,200 --> 00:28:34,190
Is it some kind of website?

369
00:28:38,140 --> 00:28:41,290
"Welcome to the Takasato
Elementary Forest!"

370
00:28:41,400 --> 00:28:42,730
Is this...?

371
00:28:46,200 --> 00:28:48,350
Takasato Elementary Forest?

372
00:28:48,990 --> 00:28:51,930
"Comic book cafe"

373
00:29:18,550 --> 00:29:22,760
"Welcome to the Takasato
Elementary Forest!"

374
00:29:33,900 --> 00:29:37,200
"Imakuni"

375
00:29:52,390 --> 00:29:53,220
Hey.

376
00:29:56,840 --> 00:29:57,980
Took you long enough.

377
00:30:09,500 --> 00:30:10,640
King...

378
00:30:11,360 --> 00:30:14,060
Yukki, Toyo...

379
00:30:15,650 --> 00:30:16,990
Sorry, I just...

380
00:30:17,280 --> 00:30:19,620
Save it.

381
00:30:21,180 --> 00:30:21,800
Right?

382
00:30:23,310 --> 00:30:23,870
Yeah.

383
00:30:25,830 --> 00:30:27,900
This is what matters right now.

384
00:30:33,040 --> 00:30:34,200
Is this...?

385
00:30:35,020 --> 00:30:37,780
There was a video left
on Chonmage’s old flip phone.

386
00:30:40,320 --> 00:30:41,400
Ready...

387
00:30:41,500 --> 00:30:43,760
One day Hin

388
00:30:43,970 --> 00:30:46,280
In the forest Kantaro

389
00:30:46,430 --> 00:30:48,400
A bear and Niko

390
00:30:48,590 --> 00:30:50,670
Met Tabo

391
00:30:50,790 --> 00:30:55,240
A forest path
in bloom with Chonmage

392
00:30:55,470 --> 00:30:59,830
A bear met Taka-King!

393
00:31:00,170 --> 00:31:00,660
Yay!

394
00:31:03,110 --> 00:31:04,040
Did you notice?

395
00:31:06,500 --> 00:31:10,690
We always thought
there were six of us.

396
00:31:12,260 --> 00:31:13,410
But that was wrong.

397
00:31:17,240 --> 00:31:18,230
Ready...

398
00:31:18,360 --> 00:31:20,700
One day Hin

399
00:31:20,850 --> 00:31:23,130
In the forest Kantaro

400
00:31:23,360 --> 00:31:25,360
A bear and Niko

401
00:31:25,500 --> 00:31:27,590
Met Tabo

402
00:31:27,710 --> 00:31:31,460
A forest path
in bloom with Chonmage

403
00:31:35,780 --> 00:31:36,740
This guy...

404
00:31:39,550 --> 00:31:40,940
There was another one.

405
00:31:44,380 --> 00:31:46,180
He’s even in the song.

406
00:31:47,140 --> 00:31:49,800
Who's inside there?

407
00:31:50,020 --> 00:31:52,920
Who's inside there?

408
00:31:56,450 --> 00:31:57,170
Let's go home.

409
00:31:57,810 --> 00:31:59,400
Come with us if you want.

410
00:32:04,080 --> 00:32:05,660
Hey, let me play the game too.

411
00:32:05,850 --> 00:32:07,790
Alright, bomb here.
Yes! Got it!

412
00:32:07,910 --> 00:32:11,530
- Oh no..
- Yes! I won!

413
00:32:12,870 --> 00:32:14,500
Well, I’m gonna head home now.

414
00:32:15,690 --> 00:32:17,520
Oh, yeah.
See you later, Mori.

415
00:32:17,880 --> 00:32:19,460
Bye-bye!

416
00:32:22,870 --> 00:32:23,810
Mori...

417
00:32:25,600 --> 00:32:27,890
Mori moved away
halfway through sixth grade.

418
00:32:28,250 --> 00:32:30,120
That's why he’s not
in the graduation album.

419
00:32:31,640 --> 00:32:34,430
We don’t know where he is now
or what he’s doing.

420
00:32:34,580 --> 00:32:36,270
- But...
- We had

421
00:32:37,200 --> 00:32:40,800
that class website, remember?
Or more like a message board.

422
00:32:42,860 --> 00:32:45,950
Apparently people were having
a great time trashing me on it.

423
00:32:47,660 --> 00:32:48,570
And

424
00:32:52,230 --> 00:32:55,250
ten days ago,
there was a new post.

425
00:32:55,870 --> 00:32:58,910
"Nobody remembers
this website... or me."

426
00:33:03,180 --> 00:33:04,330
Chonmage...?

427
00:33:05,440 --> 00:33:10,140
I don’t know if Haryu knew
about the site or just happened to find it.

428
00:33:10,790 --> 00:33:12,010
But he posted there.

429
00:33:13,390 --> 00:33:16,960
"I don't want to see King and the others.
But it's okay to see you, Chonmage."

430
00:33:17,970 --> 00:33:21,270
That’s why he didn’t say
anything to you two.

431
00:33:24,090 --> 00:33:28,270
And this was posted
just a few minutes ago.

432
00:33:28,330 --> 00:33:29,660
"Then let's meet today at 5 p.m."

433
00:33:29,710 --> 00:33:30,990
5 p.m....?

434
00:33:31,500 --> 00:33:33,980
Yes. We're running out of time.

435
00:33:34,890 --> 00:33:36,580
Finally.

436
00:33:38,050 --> 00:33:41,150
I've got a lot
I want to ask Mori.

437
00:33:44,560 --> 00:33:46,880
Toyo, are you okay?

438
00:33:50,230 --> 00:33:51,810
We’ll get to see
Chonmage too, right?

439
00:33:52,200 --> 00:33:53,480
Then of course I'm going.

440
00:33:55,740 --> 00:33:57,020
It’s dangerous, you know.

441
00:33:57,840 --> 00:34:00,750
We’re not giving up.

442
00:34:03,350 --> 00:34:04,360
What about King?

443
00:34:06,340 --> 00:34:07,450
What are you going to do?

444
00:34:17,950 --> 00:34:19,580
No good. It’s not open.

445
00:34:20,510 --> 00:34:22,150
Doesn’t look like we can get in, huh?

446
00:34:22,530 --> 00:34:24,600
I knew it. It went out of business.

447
00:34:25,880 --> 00:34:27,600
Digital probably did it in.

448
00:34:28,930 --> 00:34:30,490
Look who's talking.

449
00:34:31,050 --> 00:34:32,380
I'm kidding.

450
00:34:33,300 --> 00:34:34,580
You’re getting nervous, huh?

451
00:34:35,310 --> 00:34:36,700
That's when you go for it.

452
00:34:37,260 --> 00:34:39,790
But isn’t there some light on?

453
00:35:00,790 --> 00:35:03,320
Hey, King.
What’s the plan?

454
00:35:03,870 --> 00:35:07,090
We find Chonmage.
We grab Mori. That's it.

455
00:35:55,900 --> 00:35:56,640
Ah!

456
00:36:00,580 --> 00:36:01,620
Hakase...?

457
00:36:05,870 --> 00:36:06,740
Mori?

458
00:36:20,610 --> 00:36:23,670
Let's end this.

459
00:36:39,990 --> 00:36:42,100
Where the hell are they?

460
00:36:54,240 --> 00:36:56,220
Ah, damn it!!

461
00:36:56,850 --> 00:36:59,210
Ah! You promised!

462
00:37:05,610 --> 00:37:06,850
Mori!

463
00:37:22,310 --> 00:37:24,520
Why did you kill them?!

464
00:37:25,420 --> 00:37:26,460
Chonmage?

465
00:37:27,860 --> 00:37:28,740
I'll...

466
00:37:29,934 --> 00:37:31,767
I'll end this!!

467
00:37:32,150 --> 00:37:33,240
Chonmage!

468
00:37:38,190 --> 00:37:40,200
Aah!

469
00:37:41,000 --> 00:37:42,670
Stop!

470
00:37:43,160 --> 00:37:44,220
Damn it!

471
00:37:46,450 --> 00:37:47,250
Ahh...!

472
00:37:47,970 --> 00:37:49,750
I won't let you get away!

473
00:37:59,070 --> 00:37:59,870
Hey!

474
00:38:01,620 --> 00:38:03,770
Haryu! Haryu!

475
00:38:09,420 --> 00:38:11,270
Ah... everyone...

476
00:38:13,490 --> 00:38:14,500
Sorry...

477
00:38:15,330 --> 00:38:16,550
He got away.

478
00:38:18,110 --> 00:38:19,930
Chonmage, you...

479
00:38:20,270 --> 00:38:22,810
Go after the one who ran. Quick!

480
00:38:24,070 --> 00:38:25,560
Got it. Okay...

481
00:38:25,700 --> 00:38:28,070
Chonmage, hang on a sec!

482
00:38:32,010 --> 00:38:33,270
Be careful.

483
00:38:36,030 --> 00:38:38,080
- Where'd Toyo go?
- The other side!

484
00:38:38,160 --> 00:38:41,030
- Got it! Watch yourself!
- Yeah!

485
00:38:42,430 --> 00:38:44,110
Hey, there he is!

486
00:38:47,000 --> 00:38:48,840
Damn it!

487
00:38:52,030 --> 00:38:54,580
- Yukki, I need you!
- Just come, fast!

488
00:39:02,770 --> 00:39:04,180
Where is he?

489
00:39:05,960 --> 00:39:06,830
Hey!

490
00:39:10,410 --> 00:39:12,580
Sorry! I’m counting
on you for the rest!

491
00:39:12,890 --> 00:39:14,700
- Are you okay?
- Yeah. Sorry!

492
00:39:14,790 --> 00:39:15,580
It's okay!

493
00:39:23,650 --> 00:39:25,160
Are you okay?

494
00:39:29,920 --> 00:39:31,580
We should call the police.

495
00:39:32,520 --> 00:39:33,860
It’s my fault.

496
00:39:35,280 --> 00:39:35,940
Huh?

497
00:39:37,490 --> 00:39:40,250
Because of me, Mori...

498
00:39:42,610 --> 00:39:43,690
So...

499
00:39:45,350 --> 00:39:47,000
I have to end this.

500
00:39:47,300 --> 00:39:48,000
Huh...

501
00:39:48,140 --> 00:39:49,200
Haryu!

502
00:39:49,950 --> 00:39:50,960
Haryu!

503
00:39:53,920 --> 00:39:55,090
Haryu!

504
00:39:56,730 --> 00:39:57,950
Haryu!

505
00:40:15,200 --> 00:40:16,210
I...

506
00:40:17,370 --> 00:40:18,960
I’ll end this.

507
00:40:27,050 --> 00:40:28,490
Hey! Wait up, you!

508
00:40:30,390 --> 00:40:31,510
- Whoa!
- Whoa!

509
00:40:32,620 --> 00:40:34,310
Huh? Why?

510
00:40:37,060 --> 00:40:39,430
Huh? What the...?

511
00:41:03,520 --> 00:41:04,320
Mori?

512
00:41:06,780 --> 00:41:08,290
That's you, Mori, right?

513
00:41:12,060 --> 00:41:12,910
King!

514
00:41:13,890 --> 00:41:15,260
Right there!

515
00:41:20,730 --> 00:41:21,950
Mori!

516
00:41:25,020 --> 00:41:25,840
Mori!

517
00:41:26,700 --> 00:41:28,540
Mori! Hang on!

518
00:41:29,310 --> 00:41:30,520
I’m counting on you, King!

519
00:41:44,880 --> 00:41:47,450
- Go, King, go!
- You've got this!

520
00:42:06,970 --> 00:42:09,000
Go for it, King!

521
00:42:09,540 --> 00:42:10,900
I’m counting on you, King.

522
00:42:11,080 --> 00:42:13,420
Next time, you're
definitely winning, right?!

523
00:42:30,350 --> 00:42:31,530
Damn it!!

524
00:42:34,710 --> 00:42:35,700
King!

525
00:42:36,360 --> 00:42:37,740
Sorry, he got away!

526
00:42:38,260 --> 00:42:39,630
Seriously?

527
00:42:39,820 --> 00:42:42,970
He must be on the track team
or something, that bastard!

528
00:42:47,340 --> 00:42:50,010
Did you see his face?

529
00:42:50,560 --> 00:42:52,440
Not really...

530
00:42:52,740 --> 00:42:54,200
Ah, damn it!

531
00:42:56,390 --> 00:42:58,020
It's not over yet.

532
00:42:59,710 --> 00:43:01,340
We won't lose next time!

533
00:43:04,390 --> 00:43:05,990
We're gonna win next time!

534
00:43:07,230 --> 00:43:09,390
We're definitely gonna win!

535
00:43:16,190 --> 00:43:18,560
Yeah. Right?

536
00:43:19,440 --> 00:43:20,360
Yeah.

537
00:43:22,560 --> 00:43:23,360
Yukki.

538
00:43:28,140 --> 00:43:29,320
I mean it.

539
00:43:34,540 --> 00:43:35,590
